ass="attachment-full size-full wp-post-image" alt="Mike Portnoy of Dream Theater performs onstage at Stockholm Waterfront on November 08, 2024 in Stockholm, Sweden. (Photo by Iwi Onodera/Getty Images)" decoding="async" loading="lazy" srcset="https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/01/Dream-Theaters-Mike-Portnoy-performing.jpg 2000w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/01/Dream-Theaters-Mike-Portnoy-performing-400x254.jpg 400w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/01/Dream-Theaters-Mike-Portnoy-performing-800x508.jpg 800w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/01/Dream-Theaters-Mike-Portnoy-performing-696x442.jpg 696w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/01/Dream-Theaters-Mike-Portnoy-performing-1392x884.jpg 1392w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/01/Dream-Theaters-Mike-Portnoy-performing-1068x678.jpg 1068w" sizes="auto, (max-width: 2000px) 100vw, 2000px" /></p><p> <a href="/artists/Dream-Theater">Dream Theater</a> have released their new song &#39;Midnight Messiah&#39; from their upcoming album &#39;Parasomnia&#39;.</p><ul class="post-content-read-more"><li> <strong>READ MORE: <a href="https://www.nme.com/lists/end-of-year/best-albums-2024-3818995">NME&#39;s 50 Best Albums of 2024</a></strong></li></ul><p> “Midnight messiah / Darkness descends / Eternally wired / The dream never ends / Twilight desires / Midnight messiah,” sings frontman James LaBrie over pulsing and thrashing drums and chugging guitars.</p><p> The track features a lyrical contribution from drummer Mike Portnoy, marking the first time that he has contributed to the lyrics since 2009. Portnoy returned to the band in 2023 following a 13-year absence from the group.</p><p> Speaking about &#39;Midnight Messiah&#39; in a press release, Portnoy said: “It was great writing lyrics again and contributing this chapter to the Parasomnia story. DT粉丝可能会从发现我过去许多DT歌词的歌曲中发现的一些隐藏的掘金，而音乐视频是我们最近在欧洲整个欧洲和欧洲完成的前两个巡回演出腿的兴奋的很好的代表。南美洲。正好及时为我们整个北美的下一条腿做准备，我们很高兴能开始。” </p><p><iframe loading="lazy" title="梦想剧院 - 午夜弥赛亚（官方视频）" width="696" height="392" src="https://www.youtube.com/embed/JwOjMJB0Q2k?feature=oembed&enablejsapi=1" frameborder="0" allow="accelerometer; autoplay; clipboard-write; encrypted-media; gyroscope; picture-in-picture; web-share" referrerpolicy="strict-origin-when-cross-origin" allowfullscreen></iframe></p><p> The track is featured in Dream Theater&#39;s upcoming 16th album &#39;Parasomnia&#39; which is set for release on February 7 via InsideOut. You can pre-order it <a href="https://dream-theater.lnk.to/ParasomniaAlbum?fbclid=PAZXh0bgNhZW0CMTEAAaZOmtY8dDnzsP5uzlYBbhX5IxIeuI-FTQOK7UIfXpB8YTwe-bdUNe1KQe4_aem_PXa_q9WsWLkrKlIeyJh7LQ" target="_blank" rel="noopener">here</a> . &#39;Parasomnia&#39; marks the first LP to feature the band&#39;s iconic line-up of Portnoty, LaBrie, John Petrucci, John Myung and Jordan Rudess.</p><p> The LP was produced by Petrucci, engineered by James &#39;Jimmy T&#39; Meslin, and mixed by Andy Sneap. &#39;Parasomnia&#39; will be available as a limited-edition deluxe box set, a 2xLP 180g gatefold vinyl pressing with a 12-page booklet a special edition CD Digipak and a digital album which includes Dolby Atmos – mixed by Mark Gittins.</p><p> Dream Theater are set to embark on their 2025 North American 40th-anniversary tour next month. Check out a full list of tour dates below and visit <a href="https://ticketmaster.evyy.net/c/2862475/264167/4272?sharedid=NME&amp;u=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ticketmaster.com%2Fdream-theater-tickets%2Fartist%2F744581" target="_blank" rel="noopener">here</a> to purchase tickets.</p><h2> <strong>Dream Theater&#39;s &#39;An Evening With Dream Theater 40th Anniversary Tour 2025&#39; North American dates are:</strong></h2><p><strong>二月</strong><br /><strong>7 – Philadelphia, PA – The Met</strong><br /> <strong>8 – Raleigh, NC – Martin Marietta Center</strong><br /> <strong>10 – Nashville, TN – Opry House</strong><br /> <strong>11 – Atlanta, GA – Coca-Cola Roxy</strong><br /> <strong>12 – 